cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CC

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) and focuses on distinguishing between antonyms and synonyms. Additionally, the use of neural networks and lexico-syntactic patterns further supports this categorization. 

The paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development of a neural network model for NLP tasks. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper utilizes neural networks in its approach. 

Finally, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) could be a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with computational complexity, but rather focuses on improving the performance of NLP systems.
